        public void SubmitBuffer(byte[] buffer)

      • SubmitBuffer

        public void SubmitBuffer(byte[] buffer,
                int offset,
                int count)
        Submits an audio buffer for playback. Playback begins at the specified offset, and the byte count determines the size of the sample played.
        Parameters:
        buffer - Buffer that contains the audio data. The audio format must be PCM wave data.
        offset - Offset, in bytes, to the starting position of the data.
        count - Amount, in bytes, of data sent.
        Throws:
        ObjectDisposedException
        ArgumentException
